    HARD DISKS AND THE FLOPPY:


       If you have 1 IDE hard disk,  then you simply find out a 
way to  place it orizontally (or vertically if you like,  but I 
didn't feel to do it). I had some problems, 'cause I had 2 hard 
disks and I had to place quite  far from the motherboard.  So I 
used another IDE plain cable (40p) and 3 connectors (1 male and 
2 female) and I connected it to the old one which is  (too bad) 
miniIDE(female)-->IDE(female). This is the scheme:



