       For the floppy led you can also  do the  same thing,  but 
you surely won't have any led (unless you use the turbo one)  on
your case tower. So I used the led in the PC drive mask. 



    THE POWER SUPPLY:


       On a PC power supply, you can  find many cables.  Most of 
them are simply 4 pins connectors (the bigger ones for HDs,  CD-
ROMs etc, and the other ones for floppy drives). You'll find out 
also 2 other connectors (named P8 and P9), which are, instead, 6
pins. Some people told me that these P8 and P9 connectors aren't
always the same so I suggest you to find every voltage you  need
using an amperometer (a tester).
   


